Detailed Description

Create status for the M2M create call. This should be passed to the create function as a create status argument while creating the driver.

sturct Vps_M2mCreateStatus

Field Documentation

UInt32 Vps_M2mCreateStatus::maxChPerHandle

Maximum number of channels that can be supported/submitted per handle. Note that the the maximum number of channels will be shared between handles if more than one handle is opened. This is to avoid unnecessary wastage memory allocation.

UInt32 Vps_M2mCreateStatus::maxHandles

Maximum number of handles supported by driver per instance.

UInt32 Vps_M2mCreateStatus::maxSameChPerRequest

Maximum number of same channels that can be submitted for processing per request.

Int32 Vps_M2mCreateStatus::retVal

Return value of create call.
